1-) installation mariadb (database)
    - Folder type: There must be a docker file into the srcs/requirements/mariadb/
    - dockerfile: install a mariadb using an alphine-based images
2-) wordpress + PHP-FPM installation
    - Folder type: There must be a docker file into the srcs/requirements/wordpress
        and also a script file that will be automatically set up
    - Connection: must be connected to the mariadb container
    - Functionality: must be able to install wordpress and configure it
3-) Update Docker compose file:
    - services: must be updated to include mariadb and wordpress services
    - volumes: must be updated to include mariadb and wordpress volumes
    - networks: be sure that all containers are connected to the same network "inception"
4-) Missing documentation:
    - README.md: must be updated to include the new configuration
    - USER-DOC.md: It is a guide for users.
    - DEV-DOC.md: It is a guide for developers.